HEADWORD: Gammadion
<hw>Gam*ma"di*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A cross formed of
four capital gammas, formerly used as a mysterious ornament on
ecclesiastical vestments, etc. See <er>Fylfot</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gamma ray</ent>⟦br⟧
